England Beats West Indies by 10 Wickets in Opening Twenty20 Game

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-23T20:10:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/england-beats-west-indies-by-10-wickets-in-opening-twenty20-game.html
England  beat the West Indies by 10
wickets to open their two-game Twenty20 cricket series.  Alex Hales was 62 not out and  Craig Kieswetter  scored an
unbeaten 58 as England reached its target of 126 in 15.2 overs
at the Oval in London. The reigning Twenty20 world champions
finished 128-0 for their first 10-wicket win in the gameâ€™s
shortest form.  Ravi Bopara took 4-10, the best bowling figures for England
in a Twenty20 game, as the West Indies were restricted to 125
all out after being put into bat. Johnson Charles scored 36 and
Dwayne Smith had 33 West Indies, which collapsed after reaching
97-3.  The series concludes in two days at the Oval.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
